> >Harbor Freight has a 40 pound pressurized sand blaster on sale for $80.
> >Anyone have one or Used One?  Are they any good? I have one of their
venturi
> >type units that sucks the sand out of a bag. It sure is slow. Is the
> >pressurized unit better?
>
> Night and Day better, it holds 100 # of sand and will take 175 psi .
> Much more force when there is pressure behind the sand, and it
> doesn't take any away from the output. Forget the nozzles, they
> are no good. Get a better, bigger one. It has 3 valves to control
> air and sand, these wear out as well as the hose and the
> sand fitting in the base. But basically a good deal.
> Dave\X/
